Third Point LLC Key Developments

Third Point Encourages Nestlé To Sell Off Its Stake In L'Oréal
Jun 26 17
A hedge fund owned by Dan Loeb, Third Point LLC, has built a $3.5 billion stake in Nestlé S.A. (SWX:NESN) and is encouraging Nestlé to sell off its stake in L'Oréal S.A. (ENXTPA:OR), as well as what it deems nonessential operations, including the U.S. confectionery business.


Third Point Urges Nestlé To Seek Acquisition
Jun 26 17
Dan Loeb’s Third Point LLC issued a letter on June 25, 2017 stating that it now owns about 40 million shares in Nestlé S.A. (SWX:NESN) which is in the process of moving its U.S. headquarters to Rosslyn, Va. - and laid out its intentions to set the company on a new course "with a greater sense of urgency." "Nestle has fallen behind over the past decade in an environment where growth has slowed due to changes in consumer tastes and shopping habits, as well as an influx of new competition from smaller, local brands," Third Point wrote in the letter. Third Point said it is "past time" for Nestle to undertake a comprehensive portfolio review of its more than 2,000 brands in food and beverage and health-science fields. It is urging the company to pursue acquisitions in "high growth and advantaged categories."


Third Point LLC Presents at Credit Suisse Asia Investment Conference, Apr-07-2016 02:00 PM
Apr 1 16
Third Point LLC Presents at Credit Suisse Asia Investment Conference, Apr-07-2016 02:00 PM. Venue: Conrad Hotel, Hong Kong, Hong Kong. Speakers: Munib Islam, Partner.


